/*
2015 05 28

This Sketch emulates 1970's consoles which used the AY-3-8500 chip
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AY-3-8500
These console have usually 6 games: Tennis Soccer, Squash, Practice and two Rifle games.
Tennis the same as Pong.
See the Grant page for more informations.

Rifle games are not emulates because they require a CRT TV set and doesn't work on LCD.
Moreover they require a simulated rifle with a switch and a LDR.

Adapted for Funduino Joystick Shield by zoomx
(but is much better to use paddles!)
Fixed scanLine = -1; on the cutted TVout library

REMEMBER: THE ORIGINAL USE PIN10 INSTEAD OF PIN 7 AS IN STANDARD TVOUT
THIS ONE WAS MODIFIED TO USE PIN7 THE SAME OF TVOUT!
You don't need the TVout library since is included in this sketch.

Some changes to do for some selection since the original
sketch uses switch instead of buttons

Changed speed ball code because with the previous
I got the ball at full speed.

Video= pin7
Sync= pin10
Audio= pin 11  (to check!)
These are defined in the TV out part of this sketch.
*/

